<h4>Day 3: Experience a calmer kitchen by stowing inactive appliances in cabinets and drawers.</h4>
<blockquote class="instagram-media" style="background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width: 658px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);" data-instgrm-captioned="" data-instgrm-version="5">
<div style="padding: 8px;">
<div style="background: #F8F8F8; line-height: 0; margin-top: 40px; padding: 37.5% 0; text-align: center; width: 100%;"></div>
<p><a href="https://instagram.com/p/8YwzOpIyHX/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'https://instagram.com/p/8YwzOpIyHX/', '#MinimalismTips Day 3: Experience a calmer kitchen by stowing inactive appliances in cabinets and drawers. Once you’ve let go of all your unneeded, unused, and redundant contraptions, store lesser-used kitchen implements—blenders, food processors, cutting boards—out of sight, which’ll declutter your counters and allow you to enjoy the aesthetics of your home. What items currently clutter your kitchen counters? Do you use them? If not, donate them to someone who can. Or, if you use them sporadically, put them away and let your countertops breathe. (Author’s note: before washing your George Foreman Grill, pretreat it by throwing it away.)']);" style="color: #000; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 17px; text-decoration: none; word-wrap: break-word;"  target="_blank">#MinimalismTips Day 3: Experience a calmer kitchen by stowing inactive appliances in cabinets and drawers. Once you’ve let go of all your unneeded, unused, and redundant contraptions, store lesser-used kitchen implements—blenders, food processors, cutting boards—out of sight, which’ll declutter your counters and allow you to enjoy the aesthetics of your home. What items currently clutter your kitchen counters? Do you use them? If not, donate them to someone who can. Or, if you use them sporadically, put them away and let your countertops breathe. (Author’s note: before washing your George Foreman Grill, pretreat it by throwing it away.)</a> A photo posted by The Minimalists (@theminimalists) on <time style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px;" datetime="2015-10-03T19:18:52+00:00">Oct 3, 2015 at 12:18pm PDT</time>
</div>
</blockquote>
