<h4>Day 14: The price of our material possessions extends well beyond the price tag.</h4>
<blockquote class="instagram-media" style="background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width: 658px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);" data-instgrm-captioned="" data-instgrm-version="5">
<div style="padding: 8px;">
<div style="background: #F8F8F8; line-height: 0; margin-top: 40px; padding: 37.5% 0; text-align: center; width: 100%;"></div>
<p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0; padding: 0 4px;"><a href="https://instagram.com/p/803qFFIyE3/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'https://instagram.com/p/803qFFIyE3/', '#MinimalismTips Day 14: The price of our material possessions extends well beyond the price tag. As a society, our homes are larger than ever, and yet we have accumulated so much stuff that we’ve created a pernicious $22 billion storage industry, which continues to expand each year. Last year, Americans spent more on storage than we did on entertainment—we are forsaking experiences for unused trinkets. Not only do our material items gobble up our money, they rob us of our most precious resources: our time and attention. How might your finances, time, and experiences be different if you were to consume more intentionally?']);" style="color: #000; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 17px; text-decoration: none; word-wrap: break-word;"  target="_blank">#MinimalismTips Day 14: The price of our material possessions extends well beyond the price tag. As a society, our homes are larger than ever, and yet we have accumulated so much stuff that we’ve created a pernicious $22 billion storage industry, which continues to expand each year. Last year, Americans spent more on storage than we did on entertainment—we are forsaking experiences for unused trinkets. Not only do our material items gobble up our money, they rob us of our most precious resources: our time and attention. How might your finances, time, and experiences be different if you were to consume more intentionally?</a></p>
<p style="color: #c9c8cd; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 8px; overflow: hidden; padding: 8px 0 7px; text-align: center; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;">A photo posted by The Minimalists (@theminimalists) on <time style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px;" datetime="2015-10-14T17:17:31+00:00">Oct 14, 2015 at 10:17am PDT</time></p>
