<h4>Day 24: Embrace the junk drawer.</h4>
<blockquote class="instagram-media" style="background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width: 658px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);" data-instgrm-captioned="" data-instgrm-version="5">
<div style="padding: 8px;">
<div style="background: #F8F8F8; line-height: 0; margin-top: 40px; padding: 50.0% 0; text-align: center; width: 100%;"></div>
<p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0; padding: 0 4px;"><a href="https://instagram.com/p/9OZnMLoyFk/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'https://instagram.com/p/9OZnMLoyFk/', '#MinimalismTips Day 24: Embrace the junk drawer. We all need a place to store our miscellanea, but that doesn\'t mean it has to be chaotic, overflowing, overwhelming. Here\'s an idea: what if you had only one junk drawer, and you filled it with whatever you want, but you cleared it out every 90 days, freeing it of unused junk? Would you find more value—and less stress—in the drawer\'s existence? Perhaps we shouldn\'t call it a &quot;junk drawer,&quot; then. How about a &quot;curated drawer&quot;? With the excess out of the way, that sounds more apropos, doesn\'t it? How about you: could your junk drawer use a little curation?']);" style="color: #000; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 17px; text-decoration: none; word-wrap: break-word;"  target="_blank">#MinimalismTips Day 24: Embrace the junk drawer. We all need a place to store our miscellanea, but that doesn&#8217;t mean it has to be chaotic, overflowing, overwhelming. Here&#8217;s an idea: what if you had only one junk drawer, and you filled it with whatever you want, but you cleared it out every 90 days, freeing it of unused junk? Would you find more value—and less stress—in the drawer&#8217;s existence? Perhaps we shouldn&#8217;t call it a &#8220;junk drawer,&#8221; then. How about a &#8220;curated drawer&#8221;? With the excess out of the way, that sounds more apropos, doesn&#8217;t it? How about you: could your junk drawer use a little curation?</a></p>
